Occult paravalvular leak in a clinically normal St. Jude's mitral valve presenting with life-threatening microangiopathic hemolytic anemia.
 A case of microangiopathic hemolytic anemia associated with a St.
 Jude Medical prosthetic paravalvular valve leak, not detected by echocardiography or cardiac angiography and requiring thoracotomy for diagnosis and therapy is described.
 The importance of considering the presence of a paravalvular leak in a patient with MAHA and a prosthetic valve even with a negative invasive cardiac work-up is discussed.
